review:
/// TLDR: The last real Indiana Jones game for PC as of 2020. Every Indiana Jones fan should play and finish this before Angel of Death arrives. ///


I have played this LucasArts game in 2011&2012, collecting all artifacts in the process. The storyline is LONG enough to make it worth your purchase tenfold. You will travel into vastly different places through your adventure. The fighting mechanics is incredibly good and satisfying. During your fights, you will feel as Dr. Jones himself; sweating with every fist and whip move you try to achieve. There are multiple fighting combos embedded in game which are really fun and worth the try. Once you learn how to fight and use your whip, game fun will be UNLOCKED. Ambient sounds and background music are nothing short of a serious Hollywood film. The weird comedy factor found in all Indy Films also exists here. Character voices are spot-on, nothing cringy. Not all levels are easy to finish and it adds to the overall realism. Sometimes it is about brainpower, sometimes it is about examining surroundings, sometimes it is all about rushing somewhere or someone. The monster bestiary is wider than you want. I have found a much better game than i expected even before reaching final levels and bosses. Graphics quality is still good enough to beset your perspectives. 

The only downside of this game is that most of those currently available adventure games will not seem as good after you finish Indiana Jones® and the Emperor's Tomb™.
